final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First determine that the green object is the Goal object. Since there is an opening in the enclosure at (18, 8), we need to align the agent on the horizontal axis (y=8) by not doing anything because it's already aligned. Next, move the agent to pick up the Key by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5 and the yellow object is at x=13, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times. Then, move the agent to reach the KeyDoor by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is now at x=13, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times. Now that the agent has the Key and is in front of the KeyDoor, it can open the KeyDoor by moving RIGHT once. Finally, move the agent to reach the goal (x=19) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is now at x=18, it must move RIGHT 19 - 18 = 1 time.
